description:
&lt;p&gt;Are you a Mental Health Nurse, Social Worker or Occupational Therapist interested in working within our specialist CAMHS services? We have a variety of exciting substantive opportunities available across Sussex.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Due to service transformation within the urgent and emergency care pathway for children and young people living within Sussex, we have substantive posts available in North West Sussex (NWS), Coastal West Sussex (CWS), Brighton and Hove and East Sussex. The opportunities below are grouped by geographical area; please view the opportunities available within your chosen geographical area listed below.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt;Please note; you must have a core mental health professional qualification and be registered with a professional body to be eligible to apply for these positions. Please state the area / role you are interested in applying for in the supporting information.&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;CAMHS Mental Health Liaison Practitioner A and E liaison&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have exciting opportunities in West Sussex for Band 6 and Band 7 CAMHS A&amp;E Liaison Practitioners. These roles include:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;strong&gt; A&amp;E Liaison Practitioner post to work in Worthing and Chichester hospitals&lt;/strong&gt;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The CAMHS A&amp;E liaison practitioners will be supporting Worthing and Chichester Hospitals and will be part of a developing service supporting young people presenting at A&amp;E or on the wards.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;These roles will work closely with Specialist CAMHS, Urgent Help Service, Sussex Family Eating Disorder Service and the Urgent Home Treatment Teams in West Sussex. There are clear pathways between all services that hold young people at the heart of their assessments and interventions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The teams will also provide Consultation to A and E and the wards, signposting to local services and training sessions.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;This post offers a Golden Hello, or a Relocation package up to a maximum of £2000. (pro rata applies and subject to terms and conditions. Please see attached Protocol document).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;NameSamantha RogersJob titleProject LeadEmail addresssamantha.rogers@sussexpartnership.nhs.ukAdditional contact information&lt;/p&gt;
